
[1]hateful

   HA'TEFUL, a. Odious; exciting great dislike, aversion or disgust. All
   sin is hateful in the sight of God and of good men.

   1. That feels hatred; malignant; malevolent.

   And, worse than death, to view with hateful eyes

   His rival's conquest.
